cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the problem of two mobile entities (robots) in the plane, which is a classic problem in robotics (cs.RO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The focus is on the impact of persistent memory on the problem, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents protocols for rendezvous in different settings, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
